Telemetry Collection Workflow

A telemetry collection workflow was implemented to gather operational metrics from edge devices.

Collected metrics include:

* CPU utilisation
* memory utilisation
* device temperature
* device identifier
* collection timestamp

Implemented behaviour:

* configurable collection intervals
* simulated telemetry generation
* Raspberry Pi compatibility support
* metric validation
* telemetry payload generation

This established the data collection layer required for edge monitoring.

⸻

Telemetry Submission Workflow

A telemetry submission workflow was implemented to send collected metrics to the Monitoring Service.

Target endpoint:

POST /api/v1/monitoring/telemetry

Implemented behaviour:

* telemetry payload creation
* API Gateway integration
* Monitoring Service communication
* successful response handling
* failure response handling
* retry support
* structured logging

Validated telemetry fields included:

* CPU usage
* memory usage
* temperature
* device ID
* timestamp information

This enabled real telemetry data to flow into the monitoring platform.

⸻

Heartbeat Integration Workflow

A heartbeat workflow was implemented to allow edge devices to maintain operational status within the Device Service.

Target endpoint:

POST /api/v1/devices/heartbeat

Implemented behaviour:

* heartbeat payload generation
* timestamp creation
* ONLINE status updates
* device tracking support
* heartbeat persistence
* communication failure handling

This established continuous device availability tracking.

